    <briefdescription>
<para>Global registry for component lifecycle function pointers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>`ComponentOpsRegistry` provides O(1) lookup of `ComponentOps` by `ComponentTypeId`. It uses a type-indexed vector where the index corresponds to the component type&apos;s unique identifier.</para>
<para>## Domain Scoping</para>
<para>The registry is templated on `THandle` so that each domain (identified by its `EntityHandle&lt;TStrongId&gt;` specialisation) has its own independent, `inline static` ops storage. This prevents lifecycle hooks registered for one domain from interfering with another.</para>
<para>## Usage</para>
<para>```cpp // Registration (done by <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1ecs_1_1ComponentReflector" kindref="compound">ComponentReflector&lt;THandle, TEM&gt;</ref>) ComponentOpsRegistry&lt;GameHandle&gt;::setOps(typeId, ops);</para>
<para>// Lookup at runtime const auto&amp; ops = ComponentOpsRegistry&lt;GameHandle&gt;::ops(typeId); if (ops.onAcquire) { ops.onAcquire(rawComponent); } ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Not thread-safe. All registration must complete before concurrent access.</para>
</simplesect>
